<DOC><DOCNO> AP880917-0107 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-17-88 1249EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u w PM-Reagan-Olympics     09-17 0235</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Reagan-Olympics,230</SECOND><HEAD>Reagan Salutes U.S. Olympic Athletes</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Reagan today saluted America'sOlympic athletes, calling them ``as patriotic as the Pledge ofAllegiance, as red, white and blue as the flag.''   ``Our athletes are a remarkable group, not only for theirachievements, but also for how they represent so much of what isgood and beautiful and splendid about this sweet and promisedland,'' the president said in his weekly radio address.   As he has in most of his recent radio speeches, the presidentmentioned Republican presidential nominee George Bush, saying thatthe vice president was ``representing all of us'' when he saw theathletes off to Seoul, South Korea, two weeks ago.   ``You can see the American spirit in the lives of every one ofour team members at these games,'' Reagan said. ``This team comesfrom all over our nation _ from the rough and tumble streets of ourbrawny cities to the quiet lanes of our vast countryside, from thesuburban hills of Southern California to riverfront towns in theMidwest.''   ``There is so much we have to be proud of in our Olympic teamthis year,'' Reagan said.   ``Our athletes have a love, a happiness and an exuberance inbeing American,'' he said. ``They're as patriotic as the Pledge ofAllegiance, as red, white and blue as the flag. They're filled withthe spirit of our land.''</TEXT></DOC>